{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9565016a-c089-443b-9339-60a3a572bd81","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐      ┌───────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md   │─────▶│  Ingestion    │─────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  (source)    │      │  Pipeline     │      │  (embeddings)  │\n└──────────────┘      └───────────────┘      └────────┬───────┘\n                                                      │\n┌──────────────┐      ┌───────────────┐               │\n│  User Query  │─────▶│  /api/ask     │───── retrieve ┘\n│  (question)  │      │  endpoint     │\n└──────────────┘      └───────┬───────┘\n                              │ top-k chunks + question\n                              ▼\n                      ┌───────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐\n                      │  LLM Prompt   │─────▶│  Answer +    │\n                      │  (grounded)   │      │  Citations   │\n                      └───────────────┘      └──────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. Ingestion Pipeline (`POST /api/documents/ingest`)\n- **Load** — Read all `*.md` files from `Docs/`\n- **Chunk** — Split each file into overlapping text chunks (~500 tokens, ~50-token overlap) using heading/paragraph boundaries\n- **Embed** — Generate vector embeddings per chunk (OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` or Azure OpenAI equivalent)\n- **Store** — Persist chunks + vectors in a vector store\n\n### 2. Vector Store\n- **Recommended:** Use `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` (the new .NET abstraction) with an in-memory provider for dev, swappable to Azure AI Search / Qdrant / PostgreSQL+pgvector for production\n- Each record: `{ id, docName, chunkIndex, text, embedding[] }`\n\n### 3. Query Endpoint (`POST /api/ask`)\n- Accept `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`\n- Embed the question with the same model\n- Retrieve top-k (3–5) nearest chunks via cosine similarity\n- Construct a grounded prompt: system message + retrieved chunks + user question\n- Call LLM (GPT-4o / Azure OpenAI) for the answer\n- Return `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }`\n\n### 4. Packages Needed\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` | Unified AI abstractions (chat client, embeddings) |\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` | Vector store abstraction |\n| `Azure.AI.OpenAI` or `OpenAI` | LLM + embedding provider |\n| `Markdig` | Parse markdown for smart chunking |\n\n### 5. Project Layout (proposed)\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Docs/                     # Source markdown files\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs    # Markdown → chunks\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs   # Orchestrates embed + store\n│   └── QAService.cs          # Retrieve + prompt + answer\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs      # Chunk record/entity\n│   ├── AskRequest.cs\n│   └── AskResponse.cs\n├── Controllers/\n│   ├── DocumentsController.cs  # Ingest endpoint\n│   └── AskController.cs        # Query endpoint\n├── Program.cs\n└── appsettings.json            # API keys, model config\n```\n\n### 6. Key Design Decisions\n- **Chunking strategy:** Heading-aware splitting keeps semantic coherence; overlap prevents losing context at boundaries.\n- **Grounding prompt:** Instruct the LLM to answer *only* from provided chunks and cite source filenames — reduces hallucination.\n- **Separation of concerns:** Ingestion and querying are independent services; re-ingestion can be triggered on doc changes without downtime.\n- **Swap-friendly vector store:** The `IVectorStore` abstraction lets you start in-memory and move to a managed service without code changes.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cec39267-dab7-4a81-b68b-6aa021953112","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with a `Docs/` folder containing markdown documentation files. The user wants a RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) plan/architecture document. They explicitly said no code.\n\nLet me create a comprehensive architecture plan.","outputTokens":1159,"requestId":"C019:A78B9:2068DA6:249E480:6A07D498"},"id":"ea5d54b7-2eb8-4078-858b-9f86dbbe3f3a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:21:34.242Z","parentId":"f413f847-327d-4832-ba4d-eacf0894b297"}
